p.q:
That, for the purposes of any Act of the present Session to make provision for a national policy for water, it is expedient to authorise—


(a) the payment out of moneys provided by Parliament of—


(i) any expenses incurred by any Minister under that Act;

(ii) any increase attributable to the provisions of that Act in the sums payable out of moneys so provided under any other enactment; and

(iii) any grants made by the Secretary of State to water authorities established under that Act;

(b) the issue out of the National Loans Fund of sums required by the Secretary of State for making loans to water authorities or the National Water Council so established;

(c) the payment into the National Loans Fund of sums received by the Secretary of State by way of repayment of the principal of, or payment of interest on, such loans;

(d) the issue out of the Consolidated Fund of sums required by the Treasury for fulfilling guarantees given by them of the repayment of the principal of, and payment of interest on, loans made to water authorities or the Council by persons other than the Secretary of State; and

(e) the payment into the Consolidated Fund of sums paid by water authorities or the Council in or towards repayment of any sums issued out of that Fund for fulfilling such guarantees and payments of interest on sums so issued.—[Mr. Eldon Griffiths.]

That, for the purposes of any Act of the present Session to make provision for a national policy for water, it is expedient to authorise—


(a) the payment out of moneys provided by Parliament of—


(i) any expenses incurred by any Minister under that Act;

(ii) any increase attributable to the provisions of that Act in the sums payable out of moneys so provided under any other enactment; and

(iii) any grants made by the Secretary of State to water authorities established under that Act;

(b) the issue out of the National Loans Fund of sums required by the Secretary of State for making loans to water authorities or the National Water Council so established;

(c) the payment into the National Loans Fund of sums received by the Secretary of State by way of repayment of the principal of, or payment of interest on, such loans;

(d) the issue out of the Consolidated Fund of sums required by the Treasury for fulfilling guarantees given by them of the repayment of the principal of, and payment of interest on, loans made to water authorities or the Council by persons other than the Secretary of State; and

(e) the payment into the Consolidated Fund of sums paid by water authorities or the Council in or towards repayment of any sums issued out of that Fund for fulfilling such guarantees and payments of interest on sums so issued.
